# AI Job Hunter — Project Rules

Local-first Electron desktop app. pnpm monorepo. React 19 + TypeScript strict mode.

## Architecture

```
packages/shared    → IPC contracts, types, Zod schemas. No React, no Node.
packages/ui        → React component library. No app logic.
packages/prompts   → AI prompt templates. Pure TS, zero deps.
packages/core/ai/data/workers → Backend (main process) only. Never import in renderer.
apps/desktop/src/renderer     → React UI. No Node.js access.
```

The renderer communicates with main ONLY via `window.api.*` (IPC bridge).

---

## Rules — violations are caught by ESLint + TypeScript

### 1. Never call window.api in UI files — use service hooks
```ts
// ❌ never in features/, routes/, components/
const data = await window.api.documents.list();

// ✅ always use service hooks from @/services/
import { useDocuments } from '@/services';
const { data, isLoading } = useDocuments();
```

### 2. Import useTranslation from the adapter, not react-i18next
```ts
// ❌ import { useTranslation } from 'react-i18next';
// ✅ import { useTranslation } from '@/lib/i18n';
```

### 3. Use motion tokens, not inline transition objects
```ts
// ❌ transition={{ duration: 0.18, ease: [0.22, 1, 0.36, 1] }}
// ✅ import { transition } from '@/lib/motion';
//    transition={transition.normal}
```

### 4. Use brand tokens, not hardcoded hex colors
```tsx
// ❌ className="text-[#c084fc] bg-[#a855f7]/15"
// ✅ className="text-brand-soft bg-brand/15"
```

### 5. Use shared UI primitives — never raw HTML for interactive elements
| Need | Component |
|------|-----------|
| Button | `@/components/ui/Button` |
| Input | `@/components/ui/Input` |
| TextArea | `@/components/ui/TextArea` |
| Dropdown | `@/components/ui/SelectDropdown` |
| Modal | `@/components/ui/ModalShell` |
| Confirm dialog | `@/components/ui/ConfirmModal` |
| Empty state | `@/components/ui/EmptyState` |
| Loading skeleton | `@/components/ui/LoadingSkeleton` |
| Card | `@/components/ui/GlassCard` |
| Page wrapper | `@/components/layout/PageShell` |
| AI stream | `@/components/ui/StreamingText` |

### 6. Data fetching — React Query via service hooks only
No `useState + useEffect` for remote data. Every IPC call has a service hook in `@/services/`.

### 7. State machines for complex flows (3+ states)
```ts
import { useMachine } from '@/hooks/use-machine';
import { aiGenerateMachine } from '@/lib/machines/ai-generate.machine';
const [state, send, { busy }] = useMachine(aiGenerateMachine, 'idle');
```

### 8. File placement
```
features/X/components/   → owned by one route
components/ui/           → shared across multiple features
services/                → all IPC + React Query hooks
lib/machines/            → state machine definitions
```

### 9. Adding a new IPC capability
1. Add to `packages/shared/src/ipc/contracts.ts`
2. Implement in `apps/desktop/src/main/ipc/router.ts`
3. Expose in `apps/desktop/src/preload/index.ts`
4. Create service hook in `apps/desktop/src/renderer/services/`

### 10. Renderer package imports
- ✅ `@ajh/ui`, `@ajh/shared`, `@ajh/prompts`
- ❌ `@ajh/core`, `@ajh/ai`, `@ajh/data`, `@ajh/workers` (main process only)

